               <head>Maʻdan al-asrār by ʻAli ibn Muḥammad ibn Jakan? al-ʻAlavī</head>
               <msContents class="https://id.loc.gov/authorities/subjects/sh85129660.html https://id.loc.gov/authorities/subjects/sh2001009476.html">
                  <summary>A comprehensive treatise on Shattarī Sufism by <persName>ʻAli ibn
								Muḥammad ibn ? al-ʻAlavī, known as Manjihr? (=Manuchihr?)
								Sayyid Jīv al-Ḥusaynī</persName>, based on the teachings of Shaykh
							<persName key="person_f8412">Faz̤l Allāh Muḥammad ibn ʻAlā al-Dīn Muḥammad
								Qāz̤in</persName>. Arranged in 61 chapters (<hi rend="italic">faṣl</hi>). The work concludes with the genealogies of Muḥammad
							Qāz̤in through 14 filiations. 
                  </summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1106-item1">
                     <author key="person_f8413">
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">ʻAli ibn Muḥammad ibn Jakan
									al-ʻAlavī Manjihr Sayyid Jīv al-Ḥusaynī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa">علی بن محمد بن جکن العلوی المعروف بمنجهر سید
									جیو الحسینی</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">Maʻdan al-asrār</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa">معدن الاسرار</title>
                     <incipit xml:lang="fa">اما بعد حمد و ثناء فراوان و سپاس و ستایش بی پایان
								مر مبدع موجودات عیانی و مخترع مکوّنات از اعیان و اخلاق و معانی
								الخ.</incipit>
                     <explicit xml:lang="fa">و حضرت ایشان خلافت از حضرت امام حسین دشت کربلا
								داشت و حضرت ایشان خلافت از حضرت اسد الله الغالب علی ابن ابیطالب کرم
								الله وجهه و حضرت ایشان خلافت از حضرت سید المرسلین محمد مصطفی صلی
								الله علیه و سلم. تم</explicit>
                     <note>
                        <p>The author describes himself on f. 3v as ʻAli ibn Muḥammad ibn
									Jakan? al-ʻAlavī, known as Manjihr? Sayyid Jīv al-Ḥusaynī. On f.
									4r, he states this book in 61 chapters is what Shaykh Qāz̤in-i
									ʻAlā has said about the Shaṭṭārī sect, and he has named it
										<title>Maʻdan al-asrār fī bayān-i khāndān-i mashrab-i
										Shaṭṭār</title>. 
                        </p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian. </textLang>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
